1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,924
<i>I wake up</i>

2
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:09,926
<i>And I text you first</i>

3
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,178
<i>Overthinking every word…</i>

4
00:00:12,262 --> 00:00:14,472
<i>A week ago, I thought my life was over.</i>

5
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:16,391
<i>Teenage girls, am I right?</i>

6
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,393
<i>But now that I'm hydrated, showered,</i>

7
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:21,521
<i>and fully restocked</i>
<i>on my supply of Lara Jean optimism,</i>

8
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:22,856
<i>I'm back to my old self.</i>

9
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:25,859
<i>Not everything's the same.</i>

10
00:00:25,942 --> 00:00:28,236
<i>Some wounds take longer to heal</i>
<i>than others.</i>

11
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,197
<i>Min Ho still won't talk to me.</i>

12
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:33,950
<i>But you know what? That's his problem.</i>

13
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:36,411
<i>Like LJ said, I can't stop living my life.</i>

14
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:40,373
<i>It's still our senior year, after all,</i>
<i>and time is flying by.</i>

15
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:42,250
It's official!
I am sailing around the world

16
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,462
on my dad's yacht
next year after graduation.

17
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,965
If you can live
with that carbon footprint, have fun.

18
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:51,176
Wow, an eco-attack?

19
00:00:51,676 --> 00:00:52,927
Yeah, I heard the insult.

20
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:54,429
I wasn't trying to hide it.

21
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:59,392
<i>Damn, now Mihee</i>
<i>and Madison have beef? What is going on?</i>

22
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:02,103
Sorry. Didn't mean to get between you two.

23
00:01:02,645 --> 00:01:03,772
Again.

24
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:06,066
Jin, come on. That's not--

25
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:09,486
Good choice.
Too bad he didn't choose you back.

26
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,246
Hey.

27
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:22,582
You okay?

28
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:24,626
I'm fine.

29
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:28,922
I feel awful about my part in this,
so if there's anything I can do to help--

30
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:31,299
You can help by staying out of it, Kitty.

31
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,094
Okay. I will.

32
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:38,890
For what it's worth, I hope you know
I never meant to blow up your spot.

33
00:01:43,144 --> 00:01:47,148
In hindsight,
I should have been honest with Jin.

34
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:50,485
I kind of get why you weren't.

35
00:01:50,985 --> 00:01:54,072
You made a big mistake,
and you couldn't take it back.

36
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:55,865
You were scared to lose him.

37
00:01:57,659 --> 00:01:58,660
And I did.

38
00:01:59,702 --> 00:02:01,663
But that's not on you.

39
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:05,416
I actually managed
to make things worse all by myself.

40
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,671
I heard about you and Min Ho.

41
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,049
I'm really sorry.

42
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,301
Thank you.

43
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:20,181
I can't believe we both went
through breakups without each other.

44
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:23,560
I miss you telling me
things are gonna be okay,

45
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:24,978
even when I know they're not.

46
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:26,980
And I miss leaning on you.

47
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:28,982
And your rock-hard abs.

48
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:32,360
Can we please hug it out?

49
00:02:40,326 --> 00:02:41,578
Let's never fight again.

50
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:43,746
Deal.

51
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,999
So…

52
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,585
What else did I miss?

53
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:51,796
Well, I applied early decision to NYU.

54
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,590
We're gonna be
in the same country for uni?

55
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:55,049
- Don't jinx it.
- Okay.

56
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:58,178
But maybe. JFK to LAX, baby!

57
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:02,515
<i>Thank God we made up.</i>

58
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:05,518
<i>But why is everyone else fighting?</i>

59
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:09,105
<i>I'm out of commission for one week,</i>
<i>and suddenly our friend group falls apart?</i>

60
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:11,024
<i>I have to fix this.</i>

61
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:17,572
Ugh!

62
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:23,203
Yuri, what are you doing?

63
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,079
Well, Yuri asked Yisoo
to critique her looks

64
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:27,165
for the Designer Breakthrough contest,
and…

65
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:30,335
I got two looks in before she said,

66
00:03:30,418 --> 00:03:33,379
"I don't get it.
Where are <i>you </i>in these designs?"

67
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,006
She told me to rethink everything.

68
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:36,925
In two days?

69
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:40,261
I know. I thought fashion week
was going to be my comeback

70
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:43,598
after the world watched me
go down in flames.

71
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:47,518
Wait, maybe that's it.

72
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:49,562
You're not rich anymore.

73
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:53,691
Uh, wow, Kitty.
Way to kick a diva when she's down.

74
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:55,068
Listen. Listen. Listen.

75
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:56,236
Kitty is right.

76
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,696
- These designs were the old you.
- Exactly.

77
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,073
Who is the new Yuri?

78
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:02,116
I don't know.

79
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,037
I can't just "find myself"
and create all-new looks in 48 hours.

80
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:09,207
Okay, well, you're not going to give up.
We can fix this.

81
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,376
Juliana can help brainstorm new concepts,

82
00:04:11,459 --> 00:04:13,294
and I'll get everyone
to pitch in and help.

83
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:17,507
How? Our friend group has more drama
than a middle school production of <i>Wicked.</i>

84
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:22,011
Well, I just mended things with Q,
so I'll just mend a little more.

85
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,889
The only drama you're gonna see
is on the runway,

86
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:27,725
because we are having this fashion show.

87
00:04:36,734 --> 00:04:39,279
<i>The mission, ten new looks, 48 hours.</i>

88
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:42,615
<i>All I need now is a crack team</i>
<i>crazy enough to pull it off.</i>

89
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:46,661
<i>With a little friendly matchmaking,</i>
<i>boom, we help Yuri blow Seoul away.</i>

90
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,373
- What have you got in mind?
- You're a fashionable dude.

91
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:52,583
- How are you with a needle and thread?
- Capable.

92
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:55,461
When you're this messy inside,
you got to tailor the outside.

93
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:57,755
Plus, my nana taught me needlepoint
when I was ten.

94
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:00,091
Wonderful. Hope she
also taught you how to play nice,

95
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:02,427
because Q and Jin will be there. Goodbye.

96
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,098
We need someone fast.

97
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:08,808
- You're looking at him.
- With scissors.

98
00:05:08,891 --> 00:05:10,351
To cut patterns.

99
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:11,728
Jin said he'd be there.

100
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:14,814
I cornered him in a boba shop
and held his oolong milk tea hostage.

101
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:18,276
- You should have led with that. I'm in.
- Great. So is Marius.

102
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:19,902
- Love you!
- Kitty…

103
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,531
I need a makeup pro.
Think you can bring it?

104
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:27,702
Uh, duh. My face is my résumé.

105
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:35,001
I need someone who can get
people's locks on lock. You'd be perfect.

106
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:37,920
Obvi. This doesn't just happen.

107
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:38,921
Great.

108
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:40,340
Can you get our model stage-ready?

109
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,842
Sorry, Kitty.
My days in the limelight are done.

110
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:44,802
Well, Yuri's are just beginning.

111
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:47,555
Come on.
You know what it's like to dream big.

112
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:52,643
Fine. I'll help behind the scenes.

113
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:57,523
We need a money man. You in?

114
00:05:57,607 --> 00:06:00,860
Sure. I help my dad
with his books at the restaurant.

115
00:06:00,943 --> 00:06:03,654
First rule of staying on budget,
stay on budget.

116
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:05,656
Great. Thank you.

117
00:06:06,157 --> 00:06:09,952
Okay. Yuri's gonna get back to me
about music, and Juliana's on visuals.

118
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,996
I've gotten everyone involved.

119
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:14,123
Even Min Ho?

120
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:20,713
I think everyone would like
to see you two make up.

121
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:25,385
Yeah, well, we said
some pretty harsh things to each other.

122
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,720
And I've texted him a few times.

123
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:29,555
He hasn't even responded.

124
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:32,392
He hasn't wanted
to talk to me much about it either.

125
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,018
Ever since his dad fired him,

126
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:37,563
he's buried himself
in the studio just making music.

127
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,065
Wait, his dad fired him?

128
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:41,401
Yeah. He's kind of going through it.

129
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:46,531
Maybe you can try reaching out again.

130
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:50,243
I hate that he's hurting.

131
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:51,828
But…

132
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:53,955
I just can't.

133
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:56,457
Welcome to the team.

134
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:34,162
That beat really sucks.

135
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,581
Is it going well?

136
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:40,501
Well, it's going.
I still have to mess with it.

137
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:45,673
You've been down at the studio
a lot lately.

138
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:50,094
Are you avoiding someone?

139
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:53,598
I'm not avoiding Kitty.

140
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:55,850
She's doing her thing and I'm doing mine.

141
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:58,519
Wouldn't it be better if you two talked?

142
00:08:00,229 --> 00:08:05,026
I don't know.
I just need to make music right now.

143
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,153
I'm not sure it’s going well.

144
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:08,988
Hey.

145
00:08:09,071 --> 00:08:10,907
You know what you need right now?

146
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,617
Deadline.

147
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:16,787
Yuri needs music for Seoul Fashion Week,

148
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:18,915
in two days.

149
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:20,666
You want to give it a try?

150
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,667
Me?

151
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,214
I don't know if I…

152
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:30,259
No… You can do it. Absolutely.

153
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:32,053
You…

154
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,931
you reinvented yourself.

155
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:37,767
It's the same for Yuri.

156
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:40,770
Okay.

157
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:43,856
I'll do it.

158
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:46,275
Yuri will really appreciate it.

159
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:48,694
Do your thing.

160
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:49,779
All right.

161
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,305
<i>Okay, we're down to 24 hours.</i>

162
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:19,809
<i>We've got our team, and yes, everyone is</i>
<i>definitely still mad at each other.</i>

163
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:21,769
<i>But I'm a matchmaker, okay?</i>

164
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:23,145
<i>Trust the process.</i>

165
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,774
- How's it going here?
- Just doing a makeup test on Q.

166
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:30,152
You're not seriously pairing
glitter with bronzer. Overkill much?

167
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,781
If you can't handle my sparkle,
hop off my rainbow.

168
00:09:35,032 --> 00:09:36,200
Is my face the rainbow?

169
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:37,535
Come on, you two.

170
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:40,830
You're like Elphaba and Glinda,
right before intermission.

171
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:42,623
Just talk it out.

172
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:46,168
Fine. Maybe Mihee can tell us
why she's been so aggro lately.

173
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,421
If you have to ask, you'll never know.

174
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:53,050
<i>Well, at least they're talking.</i>

175
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:54,552
<i>On to the boys.</i>

176
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:57,471
Kitty, would you mind telling Marius
he's sewing too loudly?

177
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:58,639
It's grating.

178
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,975
Someone's just jealous
I'm nimble with a thimble.

179
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,185
You're better at shit-stirring.

180
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:07,440
I didn't exactly have to twist Q's arm for
him to hop on the back of my bike, did I?

181
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,192
Hold on. Um, what?

182
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:12,820
Yeah. I didn't make the best decisions
when we weren't talking,

183
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:15,448
and now these two are probably
gonna never speak to me again.

184
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,867
Unless…

185
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:19,994
You want me to try?

186
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:21,954
I trust you.

187
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:27,960
Besides, there's absolutely no way that
you can make this any worse for me, so…

188
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:28,961
Okay.

189
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:30,755
Marius! Jin!

190
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:32,673
- Not now, Kitty!
- Don't!

191
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,677
<i>These people are entrenched.</i>

192
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,472
My matchmaking skills
are seriously being tested.

193
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:41,641
Well, pride is
the hardest thing to swallow.

194
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:44,769
So, what's the strategy
with that anyways, matchmaking?

195
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,771
Number one, get them in the same space.

196
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:48,939
Two, convince them
to give each other a chance,

197
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:51,067
and number three, hope for the best.

198
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,318
Interesting.

199
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,782
Speaking of matches,
are you and Min Ho ever gonna make up?

200
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:00,660
Doesn't really look like it right now.

201
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,286
And you're okay with that?

202
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:04,413
Not really.

203
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,874
It kind of feels like
my soul has been ripped apart,

204
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:09,794
and I'm slowly trying
to piece it back together.

205
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:12,046
I wish we could just
get past what happened,

206
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:14,840
but we're at an impasse.

207
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,467
Or stubborn.

208
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:19,762
Oh, I forgot to mention,

209
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,931
I'm gonna scrap
the playlist for the runway

210
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:23,933
and go with something original.

211
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:25,643
What? Do we have time for that?

212
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:28,020
Yeah, I got an old friend to help.
It's gonna be great.

213
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,605
Okay, can't wait to hear it.

214
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,775
We only have two hours
until the fitting deadline.

215
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:33,734
Wait, what?

216
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:35,861
I need more time to craft my looks.

217
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,405
There's no way I'll make that.

218
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,823
What happens if you don't?

219
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:40,408
I lose my runway models.

220
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:43,953
Do any of your old friends
happen to be runway models?

221
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:46,122
No.

222
00:11:57,007 --> 00:12:00,344
Actually, I don't want it
to be anyone from my old life.

223
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:03,597
My models should reflect who I am now.

224
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:08,728
Okay, everybody, listen up!

225
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:11,897
<i>I am</i>

226
00:12:14,775 --> 00:12:16,944
<i>I, I, I, I am…</i>

227
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:22,450
It's runway day, people!

228
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:26,370
Give me a strut, two, three!
Pop that butt, two, three!

229
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:28,873
Let's just take five.

230
00:12:30,374 --> 00:12:31,584
<i>This isn't working.</i>

231
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:35,296
<i>I need to intervene before Mihee</i>
<i>roundhouse-kicks Madison on the runway.</i>

232
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:36,630
<i>Clock's ticking.</i>

233
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,717
Hey, girl! Madison's hair is a rat's nest.

234
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:41,969
She's gonna totally embarrass herself
on the runway.

235
00:12:42,052 --> 00:12:45,639
- Can you do something?
- Mm. She is helpless.

236
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:48,976
Hey, um, Mihee's makeup is a disaster.

237
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:50,895
Can you give her a glow-up?

238
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,106
- She's lost without me.
- Totally.

239
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,817
- Okay, this one.
- Great.

240
00:12:56,901 --> 00:13:00,029
Okay, this one is all done.

241
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,656
- Ooh, lush!
- That is sick!

242
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:06,285
Okay, calm down, you guys.
Yuri made enough designs for everyone.

243
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:09,038
Matching motorcycle jackets
for you two, perhaps?

244
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,873
She designed this one for me.

245
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:12,958
Oh, unless, of course,
she obviously made it for me.

246
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:17,546
- I didn't mean to.
- Yuri, I am so sorry.

247
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,385
Holy shit.

248
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:26,722
This is it!

249
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:29,266
Okay, Kitty, remember when you told me

250
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,936
you felt like your soul
was being ripped apart?

251
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:33,938
Well, that's how I felt
when I lost everything

252
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,898
and I pieced myself back together, right?

253
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,944
That's what I should do with my look.
That's my story.

254
00:13:40,027 --> 00:13:42,863
- I love it.
- Wait, me too. Do we have enough time?

255
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:45,449
- We have to try.
- Okay, come on. Guys, come on.

256
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:52,706
Yuri!

257
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:56,919
Thank you.

258
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,547
Okay.

259
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,050
Okay, these three are good.
The boys are waiting.

260
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:04,134
On it.

261
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:07,388
<i>I think the boys need an intervention too.</i>

262
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:10,683
Okay, hustle up. Q, your pants.

263
00:14:10,766 --> 00:14:12,309
Marius, your shirt.

264
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:13,936
Jin, your jacket.

265
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,110
I think I have Marius' pants.

266
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:24,238
And I have Jin's shirt.

267
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,866
And I have Q's jacket.

268
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,326
- Kitty.
- Kathy!

269
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:32,580
Okay, don't be mad at Kitty.
She's just trying to help.

270
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:37,543
So can we please just try to be honest
for two seconds instead of playing games?

271
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:40,004
Gonna be honest about
what happened on your joyride?

272
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:42,798
If I'm being honest,
it wasn't much of a joyride.

273
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:45,885
He got me all revved up
and then cut the engine.

274
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:51,056
I'm sorry I led you on that day.
I know that must have hurt.

275
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:53,684
It… it did.

276
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:57,730
But I kind of deserved it.

277
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:03,068
Guys, look, since I came back to KISS,
I just figured that

278
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:07,364
what you lot had going on
couldn't compete with what we had.

279
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,074
But I was wrong.

280
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:13,078
And I know Q felt something for me
sophomore year.

281
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:18,334
But after our little motorcycle ride,
I know that he doesn't.

282
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:21,420
And I'm a lover, not a fighter.

283
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:24,590
So I am done trying to compete.

284
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:28,719
So why'd you run to Marius
the second we broke up?

285
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:31,388
I've been asking myself that every day.

286
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,600
Marius was the first person
I'd ever been with.

287
00:15:36,393 --> 00:15:38,479
But we had to sneak around,
and I hated that.

288
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:43,317
And this year we ended up
with another dirty little secret.

289
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:48,322
I think I wondered what it would be like
with Marius without the shame.

290
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:52,868
But as soon as I explored that, I realized
I already had exactly what I wanted.

291
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:56,080
And I'm sorry that hurt you, Jin.

292
00:15:57,247 --> 00:15:58,374
I'm really sorry.

293
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:13,597
I'll admit it, you made me look
ten times better.

294
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:16,433
I mean, you are
seriously skilled with a lip liner.

295
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:19,728
Okay, Mihee?

296
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,271
What's going on?

297
00:16:21,897 --> 00:16:23,357
The senior map?

298
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,693
You're sailing around the world?

299
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:29,071
We talked about taking a gap year
in Europe together, Mads.

300
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:31,740
But I guess you're moving on without me.

301
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,617
I was gonna surprise you.

302
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:36,453
Where do you think
my dad's yacht is taking us?

303
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,789
Us? Really?

304
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:42,501
Duh! You think I'd hit the beaches
in Mykonos without my best friend?

305
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:45,629
Without you, I'd have to be
one of those people with a selfie stick.

306
00:16:45,713 --> 00:16:47,798
We have to get matching bikinis.

307
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:48,966
Twins.

308
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:52,344
- Come here.
- Mm.

309
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:00,936
Min Ho.

310
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:07,067
File's all done.

311
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,318
Thank you.

312
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:12,114
- Do you like it?
- I don't know.

313
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,658
I just hope Yuri likes it.

314
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:15,993
Mm.

315
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,413
Then, let's go play it for them.

316
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:25,252
Who's them? What are you talking about?

317
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:27,046
Yuri and her producer.

318
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:29,506
When's this music guy getting here?

319
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:30,716
We have to get back to work.

320
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:34,261
- I know. He's coming.
- He's here.

321
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:38,599
- What?
- What is this?

322
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:41,685
It's only because we care.

323
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,481
Practice what you preach, Kitty.

324
00:17:57,034 --> 00:18:01,163
I've spent this whole day trying
to get our friends to work out their beef,

325
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:03,874
so maybe it's time we do that too.

326
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:08,295
All right.

327
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:11,840
I've apologized for what happened
on Chuseok.

328
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:17,805
But instead of hearing me out,
you've shut me out. Why?

329
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:21,475
Because, Kitty, all it took was one moment
of doubt and you were done with me.

330
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:24,645
I have enough people in my life
who treat me that way.

331
00:18:24,728 --> 00:18:26,271
That is so not fair.

332
00:18:26,355 --> 00:18:29,024
Listen, I don't have
a supportive family like you.

333
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:31,193
Lara Jean and Margot.

334
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:33,403
I have siblings I barely talk to.

335
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:35,948
A mum who's a continent away,

336
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:40,577
and a dad who tells me
I'll never be enough

337
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:42,371
every chance he gets.

338
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:45,457
I heard about what happened with him.

339
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,544
I'm sorry.
I know that must have really hurt.

340
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:52,172
But, Min Ho, I'm not your dad.

341
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:55,801
Yeah, you were supposed to be
the one person who believed in me.

342
00:18:55,884 --> 00:18:57,970
Of course I believe in you.

343
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:03,183
But sometimes I make mistakes.
I am a person who makes mistakes.

344
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,229
You've let me down too.

345
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,273
How?

346
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:11,650
I had my heart set on NYU.

347
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:16,321
But then I was reimagining
a potential future here.

348
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:17,865
With you.

349
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:19,658
Then I made one mistake,

350
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:23,287
and you gave up on us
and left me completely adrift.

351
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:25,497
I know the feeling.

352
00:19:30,085 --> 00:19:32,296
I wanted a future with you too, Kitty.

353
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:37,342
Well…

354
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:41,597
for what it's worth,
I will never regret what we had.

355
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,916
Well, thanks for trying.

356
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:12,127
I know you and Dae
had the best intentions.

357
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:16,381
But Min Ho is not willing to bend.

358
00:20:17,507 --> 00:20:18,926
I'm sorry, Kitty.

359
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:23,096
Hey, are you okay?

360
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:25,265
No.

361
00:20:26,683 --> 00:20:28,185
I don't think I can do this.

362
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:30,354
What? What do you mean?

363
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:35,359
I came out here to take in the moment,

364
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:39,071
and all I see are people
who knew me when I was rich

365
00:20:39,154 --> 00:20:43,450
and then laughed at me when
I lost everything and fell on my face.

366
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:47,788
Sure. But look at how far you've come.

367
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:54,378
I mean, life cut you down,
and you stitched yourself back together.

368
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,382
I didn't do it alone.

369
00:20:58,465 --> 00:20:59,758
None of us ever do.

370
00:21:01,134 --> 00:21:04,972
At the end of the day,
it doesn't matter who's in front of you.

371
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,850
Yuri, what matters is who's behind you.

372
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:24,658
They all showed up thanks to you.

373
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:27,494
They all showed up
because they believe in you.

374
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:33,041
Welcome to Seoul Fashion Week's
Designer Breakthrough Contest.

375
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:37,212
Presenting "Fire and Lace" by Lilly Yo.

376
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:43,969
Okay.

377
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:45,887
If I'm gonna do this,

378
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,391
there is one more thing I need
for this show to be a success.

379
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:52,227
I made you a dress
with your 18th birthday in mind

380
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,979
because I wanted to make it special,

381
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:56,815
but I don't think we should wait.
Tonight's the night.

382
00:21:56,898 --> 00:21:58,692
Oh, like me on the runway?

383
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:00,485
- No, I cannot do that right now.
- Yes.

384
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:02,029
Kitty, you can.

385
00:22:02,571 --> 00:22:06,700
Look, I know you don't feel amazing
right now, but you truly are.

386
00:22:06,783 --> 00:22:10,078
I mean, look at everything you've done
to make everyone else shine.

387
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,913
You deserve to shine too.

388
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:17,252
So go out there and blow everyone away.

389
00:22:20,255 --> 00:22:21,256
Come here.

390
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:30,182
And now, presenting
"Riches to Rags" by Yuri Han.

391
00:22:56,124 --> 00:22:57,125
Call me.

392
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:25,487
Wow, Yuri actually pulled this off.

393
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:29,718
And now, the moment
we've all been waiting for.

394
00:24:31,094 --> 00:24:35,474
I'm proud to present Seoul Fashion Week's
Designer Breakthrough Award

395
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:38,101
to someone who's not new to fashion,

396
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:41,730
but who is
an exciting new voice in our world.

397
00:24:41,813 --> 00:24:43,273
Ladies and gentlemen…

398
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:48,487
my protégé, Yuri Han!

399
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,743
Oh my God!

400
00:24:58,288 --> 00:25:01,708
Wait. Okay, wait,
you guys should come with me. Yes!

401
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:10,509
Congratulations.

402
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:20,810
Whoo!

403
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:29,277
<i>I don't know where</i>
<i>I'd be without you, Kitty.</i>

404
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:30,779
Definitely not here.

405
00:25:30,862 --> 00:25:33,323
Well, there's nowhere else I'd rather be.

406
00:25:33,406 --> 00:25:35,617
I am so proud of you.

407
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,077
Mm!

408
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:39,913
And I don't think I'm the only one.

409
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,124
- Hi.
- Hi.

410
00:25:44,292 --> 00:25:47,295
Juliana, that logo was amazing.

411
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:51,424
And all the help you gave me with
the looks, and last-minute changes…

412
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:53,468
You know I'm always down to help you.

413
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:57,305
Plus, I have some time on my hands
since Praveena and I broke up.

414
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,142
Oh, um…

415
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:02,602
Sorry, I didn't know that.

416
00:26:02,686 --> 00:26:05,272
Yeah, it was my loss. Kind of my fault.

417
00:26:06,356 --> 00:26:07,816
But I think it was right for us.

418
00:26:07,899 --> 00:26:10,902
I'm actually pretty proud
of how we handled it.

419
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:13,029
We're gonna stay friends.

420
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:16,283
You guys seemed good. What happened?

421
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,326
Uh…

422
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:24,457
She sensed that
I had feelings for someone else.

423
00:26:33,592 --> 00:26:34,718
Hey!

424
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:38,179
I heard you were the guy
behind that sick track.

425
00:26:38,847 --> 00:26:40,015
Congrats.

426
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:41,600
The audience was so into it.

427
00:26:41,683 --> 00:26:42,726
Yeah, it felt good.

428
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:45,854
Thanks, Gigi, for believing in me.

429
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:48,106
Uh, no, none of that.

430
00:26:48,648 --> 00:26:50,108
You believed in yourself.

431
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:55,238
Once you do that, you stop
expecting other people to fill that void.

432
00:26:59,534 --> 00:27:02,245
And you stop blaming them when they don't.

433
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:06,207
Kitty let you down once,

434
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:10,086
out of a million other times
she showed up for you.

435
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:13,381
That's who she is.

436
00:27:16,176 --> 00:27:18,094
Are you really ready to give up on her?

437
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:23,558
No.

438
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:28,355
I just don't know how to begin again.

439
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:29,856
I do.

440
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:34,277
Get out of your own way
and tell her how you really feel.

441
00:27:40,283 --> 00:27:41,159
<i>We did it.</i>

442
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:45,205
<i>We threaded the needle and stitched</i>
<i>our little KISS family back together.</i>

443
00:27:45,288 --> 00:27:48,166
<i>As for this matchmaker, I was a bit rusty.</i>

444
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,794
<i>But it turns out, I still got it.</i>

445
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,879
Kitty!

446
00:27:55,423 --> 00:27:58,551
Hey. Um, can I talk to you for a second?

447
00:27:58,635 --> 00:27:59,761
Yeah, for sure.

448
00:28:00,303 --> 00:28:02,389
Look, I know I've been stubborn.

449
00:28:03,682 --> 00:28:04,766
I just--

450
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:05,684
Sorry.

451
00:28:07,394 --> 00:28:08,770
Wait, it's NYU.

452
00:28:09,562 --> 00:28:10,605
My decision's in.

453
00:28:13,066 --> 00:28:14,275
That can wait.

454
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:17,028
No, please. You should check.

455
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:28,081
I got in. I got into NYU!

456
00:28:29,124 --> 00:28:30,125
That's brilliant!

457
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,585
Now you have at least one option.

458
00:28:32,669 --> 00:28:35,088
You won't be a complete layabout.

459
00:28:35,171 --> 00:28:38,216
Oh. I actually applied early decision

460
00:28:38,299 --> 00:28:41,386
just for the best chances of getting in,
so that means…

461
00:28:42,846 --> 00:28:44,389
You're going.

462
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:48,435
I'm moving to New York next year.

463
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:51,271
Congratulations, Covey.

464
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:55,024
I'm happy that
your dreams are coming true.

465
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:01,197
Um, what were you saying before?

466
00:29:03,491 --> 00:29:05,160
It's not important.

467
00:29:06,327 --> 00:29:07,954
You should go tell everyone the news.

468
00:29:08,913 --> 00:29:09,914
Okay.

469
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:17,630
<i>And I know that you would choose me</i>
<i>Over anybody else</i>

470
00:29:17,714 --> 00:29:22,761
<i>And I know that I'm the one you love</i>

471
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:28,391
<i>But then, why you go</i>
<i>And be with everybody else</i>

472
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:31,060
<i>Am I not enough, am I not enough?</i>

473
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:32,771
<i>Or am I not enough?</i>

474
00:29:32,854 --> 00:29:35,565
<i>Am I not enough? Or am I not enough?</i>

475
00:29:35,648 --> 00:29:38,401
<i>Am I not enough for now?</i>

476
00:29:40,153 --> 00:29:44,407
<i>Am I not enough, am I not enough?</i>
<i>Or am I not enough?</i>

477
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:47,410
<i>Am I not enough, am I not enough?</i>

478
00:29:47,494 --> 00:29:51,414
<i>- Am I not enough?</i>
<i>- You would choose me over anybody else</i>

479
00:29:51,498 --> 00:29:55,418
<i>Am I not enough, am I not enough?</i>
<i>Or am I not enough?</i>

480
00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:58,630
<i>Am I not enough? Or am I not enough?</i>

481
00:29:58,713 --> 00:29:59,881
<i>Am I not enough?</i>

482
00:29:59,964 --> 00:30:03,426
<i>Go and be with everybody else</i>

483
00:30:03,968 --> 00:30:05,428
<i>And I know that</i>

484
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:08,973
<i>I'm the one you want</i>

485
00:30:09,766 --> 00:30:11,309
<i>And I know that</i>

486
00:30:11,392 --> 00:30:15,271
<i>You would choose me over anybody else</i>

